18.title: "Den II"
18.author: by Richard Corben
18.appears_in: p. 17-24 in Heavy Metal, v. 5, no. 9 (Dec. 1981).
notes: "While searching for the queen's powerful stones, Den, Tarn, and the others came across the queens' guards and a pit chock full o' hungry reptiles. Once the stones were found, the group's almost futile effort to return to their ship proved nearly all for nought, when Den and the stones went tumbling off the side, as the ship took flight. Tarn, an eternal enemy of Den's, caught him and saved Den's life."

19.title: "Den II"
19.author: by Richard Corben
19.appears_in: p. 76-79 in Heavy Metal, v. 5, no. 10 (Jan. 1982).
notes: "Den and Kath have bid farewell to Neverwhere and departed for Earth. Meanwhile, old Zeg has been confronted by the evil queen, who is searching for the Nar stones."
"To be continued."

20.title: "Den II"
20.author: by Richard Corben
20.appears_in: p. 39-42 in Heavy Metal, v. 5, no. 11 (Feb. 1982).
notes: "The evil queen, having been unable to find the Nar stones, threw old Zeg out the window to his death. Meanwhile, Moda found the lost Tarn. But as they headed back home, they became lost in Muvovum."
"To be continued."

21.title: "Den II"
21.author: by Richard Corben
21.appears_in: p. 84-89 in Heavy Metal, v. 5, no. 12 (Mar. 1982).
notes: "Tarn, left alone by Moda, was attacked by a strange creature, who was in turn attacked by the unusual Muvovum folk. Now a prisoner, Tarn awoke in a cell with Moda. It looked like curtains for both of them."

22.title: "Den II"
22.author: by Richard Corben
22.appears_in: p. 21-24 in Heavy Metal, v. 6, no. 1 (Apr. 1982).
notes: "When we last saw Tarn and Moda, they were in the presence of Jord, the leader of the Muvovum people. He was accompanied by his pet, Jordella, who took an instant liking to Moda. Unfortunately, the feelings weren't mutual, and Moda threw Jordella to the ground. With that, the guards carried him off. The rest remains to be seen."
"To be continued."

23.title: "Den II"
23.author: by Richard Corben
23.appears_in: p. 21-24 in Heavy Metal, v. 6, no. 2 (May 1982).

24.title: "Den II"
24.author: by Richard Corben
24.appears_in: p. 20-23 in Heavy Metal, v. 6, no. 3 (June 1982).

25.title: "Den II"
25.author: by Richard Corben
25.appears_in: p. 12-15 in Heavy Metal, v. 6, no. 4 (July 1982).
notes: "When we last saw Tarn, he was tricked into making love by the creature Jordella, who had taken the form of Tarn's love, Muuta. After their lovemaking, the creature died, leaving poor Tarn sitting around wondering what was going to happen to him."

26.title: "Den II"
26.author: by Richard Corben
26.appears_in: p. 73-76 in Heavy Metal, v. 6, no. 5 (Aug. 1982).
notes: "When last we read, Tarn was attempting to kill himself, but was saved by a demon spirit. Meanwhile, Den, who had recently escaped a dreary, desert death, was battling with Zandor, a member of the Lorung tribe."
"To be continued."

27.title: "Den II"
27.author: by Richard Corben
27.appears_in: p. 19-24 in Heavy Metal, v. 6, no. 6 (Sept. 1982).
notes: "In our last issue, Den, who was living with the Lorung tribe, learned that Zeg was dead, Tarn had run away, and that Zegium was destroyed. Den left to search for Tarn and avenge Zeg's death."
To be continued.

28.title: "Den II"
28.author: by Richard Corben
28.appears_in: p. 19-23 in Heavy Metal, v. 6, no. 7 (Oct. 1982).
notes: "Last issue: Den continued searching for his friend Tarn. He came upon a Dramite hive of colossal size and entered the seemingly abandoned structure."
"To be continued."

29.title: "Den II"
29.author: by Richard Corben
29.appears_in: p. 20-24 in Heavy Metal, v. 6, no. 8 (Nov. 1982).
notes: "Last issue, Den had entered the Dramite hive and found Muuta. As they prepared to head for her estate, Muutaron, they were attacked by Dramites."
"To be continued."

30.title: "Den II"
30.author: by Richard Corben
30.appears_in: p. 36-41 in Heavy Metal, v. 6, no. 9 (Dec. 1982).

31.author: [No author]
notes: "When last we read, Tarn, who had become the king of the Lorungan Mts. and the Knorland Forests, returned to take his bride, Muuta. Soon after his arrival, Den discovered the Dramites' evil plans, and he, Muuta and the rest of the Minimuutan people planned their escape."
"To be continued."

32.title: "Den II"

50.title: "Le Français Errant"
50.author: Denayer ; A

notes: "Résumé: Chez Fulgura, les rumeurs de fermeture vont bien train. Pour sauver l'usine, Serge, le mécanicien et patron, a réalisé un nouveau protype selon lui 'révolutionnaire,' mais comme son pilot, Alain Chevallier, a refusé de l'essayer, ne l'estimant pas suffisamment au point, il l'a congédié."
"A suivre."

"A suivre."
